Description: Plot brain atlases as interactive 3D meshes using 'Three.js'
    via 'htmlwidgets', or render publication-quality static images through
    'rgl' and 'rayshader'. Ships with the Desikan-Killiany ('dk') cortical,
    automatic subcortical segmentation ('aseg'), and TRACULA white matter
    tract ('tracula') atlases. A pipe-friendly
    API lets you map data onto brain regions, control camera angles, toggle
    region edges, overlay glass brains, and snapshot or ray-trace the result.
    Additional atlases are available through the 'ggseg' r-universe.
    Mowinckel & Vidal-Piñeiro (2020) <doi:10.1177/2515245920928009>.
